  <h1>What we offer:</h1>

  <p>PPC Consultants:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Listen to employers regarding their specific training and staffing requirements </li>
    <li>Pre-screen job seekers to ensure a good organisational fit</li>
    <li>Provide advice, support and training to co-workers regarding a new employee’s disability</li>
    <li>Keep abreast of trends in local labour markets, including skills shortages</li>
    <li>Set up paid or unpaid work experience (insurance provided)</li>
    <li>Assist with training of new employees</li>
    <li>Mentor our job seekers in the workplace to manage changes at work and any impacts of their disability</li>
    <li>Purchase on-the-job mentoring from employers where a co-worker can support an employee</li>
    <li>Attend worksites as often as needed to support employment outcomes</li>
    <li>Partner with employers to develop better ways of supporting job seekers with a disability, injury or illness</li>
    <li>Utilise Job Access through the Employment Assistant Fund, providing employers and job seekers with workplace modifications, equipment and specialised services to minimise any impacts of disability</li>
    <li>Reward our employers for their commitment through Commonwealth Government {{#link-to 'page' 'wage-subsidies'}}Wage Subsidies{{/link-to}} </li>
  </ul>

  <p>PPC can assist where an existing employee might be having difficulty in the workplace because of a disability, through the {{#link-to 'page' 'job-in-jeopardy'}}Job in Jeopardy{{/link-to}} program. </p>

